            <article>
                <h3>Haunted History Bar Crawl</h3>
                <p>This eerie evening adventure took guests on a guided bar crawl through Cincinnati’s haunted Over-the-Rhine district. From beer halls to basements, we uncovered the city’s dark past—full of restless spirits, secret tunnels, and unsolved crimes.</p>
                <img src="https://as2.ftcdn.net/v2/jpg/11/27/32/13/1000_F_1127321380_Lm65h266fBBQfAMixTyjZ2hGK4hddB9E.jpg" alt="Close-up image of Music Hall in Cincinnati, OH">
                <p>Participants sipped craft cocktails while learning the chilling stories behind sites like (but not limited to):</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Music Hall – Once a pauper’s cemetery, this stunning landmark is said to echo with ghostly footsteps and shadowy figures.</li>
                    <li>The Lackman Building – Now a lively bar, but rumored to be haunted by former brewery workers and Prohibition-era spirits.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>Guides shared both documented history and whispered legends, creating a night of creepy fun, community, and craft drinks.</p>
                <p>Price: $25/person (inlcudes 1 drink ticket + guided tour)</p>
                <p>Date: <time datetime="2024-10-14">October 14, 2024</time></p>
            </article>
